Hemex provides support for:
 
Hemorrhoids / Varicose veinsAnal fissuresBenign prostate hypertrophyChronic laryngitis
 
The causes of hemorrhoids are similar to the causes of varicose veins: genetic weakness of the veins and/or excessive pressure on the veins due to lack of fiber in the diet, straining during defecation, pregnancy, long periods of sitting, and heavy lifting. Because the venous system that supplies the rectal area contains no valves, factors that increase venous congestion in the region can lead to hemorrhoid formation.
 
Collinsonia: Fresh root is indicated primarily for pelvic and venous congestion such as hemorrhoids, varicose veins, benign prostatic hypertrophy, and chronic laryngitis. Perhaps one of the most direct indications for Collinsonia is a hemorrhoid or constipated state due to vascular engorgement of the pelvic viscera. The most marked symptoms calling for it will be a sense of constriction, heat, and weight in the rectum, with dry, hard fecal matter. One of the first uses of Collinsonia was in the treatment of a form of laryngitis known as "Ministers Sore Throat." For this condition, it is the best agent we possess. Collinsonia combines well with Saw Palmetto for benign prostatic hypertrophy. Lack of tonicity of the blood vessels is overcome by the use of Collinsonia. In short, passive engorgement with dilated capillaries, poor portal circulation, and a lack of muscular tonicity calls for Collinsonia stone root. The key is a sense of weight and constriction in the part affected.*
 
Achieving optimum health and vitality depends on several factors: a nutritious diet, a healthy lifestyle, regular exercise, and adequate rest. Dietary supplements can also contribute to a sense of vitality and well-being by ensuring that the body receives the nutrients that are essential for good health and functioning properly.*
 
DNA Nutritionals uses simply the finest processes and ingredients to produce a superior product.
 
These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration (FDA). These products are not meant to diagnose, treat or cure any disease or medical condition. Please consult your doctor before starting any exercise or nutritional supplement program or before using these or any product during pregnancy or if you have a serious condition.    Ingredients   Supplement Facts:
